Look at this attic, it's cold and damp.

572
00:25:18,560 --> 00:25:19,800
You're still in postpartum confinement,

573
00:25:19,800 --> 00:25:21,000
how can you live here?

574
00:25:22,360 --> 00:25:24,200
We came back so suddenly,

575
00:25:24,920 --> 00:25:26,650
they were caught off guard too.

576
00:25:27,720 --> 00:25:28,780
Be understanding,

577
00:25:28,800 --> 00:25:29,960
just bear with it for a few days.

578
00:25:29,960 --> 00:25:30,820
Let me tell you,

579
00:25:31,320 --> 00:25:33,600
this isn't just about bearing with it for a few days.

580
00:25:33,600 --> 00:25:34,520
Do you know

581
00:25:34,920 --> 00:25:36,720
that the room you used to live in,

582
00:25:36,960 --> 00:25:38,560
isn't at all what Li Shuyuan said,

583
00:25:38,560 --> 00:25:40,320
about some refugee aunt from Zhabei

584
00:25:40,320 --> 00:25:41,840
who's half dead?

585
00:25:42,880 --> 00:25:44,410
Do you know who lives there?

586
00:25:44,600 --> 00:25:46,920
It's Zhang Yunqi's boss's

587
00:25:47,120 --> 00:25:48,320
mistress.

588
00:25:49,120 --> 00:25:50,000
Your cousin,

589
00:25:50,160 --> 00:25:51,480
for his own promotion,

590
00:25:53,440 --> 00:25:54,600
is using your house

591
00:25:54,760 --> 00:25:56,800
to house his boss's mistress.

592
00:25:57,400 --> 00:25:58,400
How do you know?

593
00:25:58,640 --> 00:25:59,370
How do I know?

594
00:25:59,400 --> 00:26:00,440
I asked around.

595
00:26:01,000 --> 00:26:02,080
The two kids downstairs

596
00:26:02,080 --> 00:26:03,440
told me very clearly,

597
00:26:03,440 --> 00:26:04,280
very plainly.

598
00:26:04,440 --> 00:26:05,720
And I saw with my own eyes,

599
00:26:05,720 --> 00:26:07,520
that little vixen and his boss.

600
00:26:07,840 --> 00:26:09,560
That vixen is so coquettish,

601
00:26:09,960 --> 00:26:12,020
and the boss is incredibly arrogant.

602
00:26:12,280 --> 00:26:14,540
What else did the vixen say to the old man?

603
00:26:14,760 --> 00:26:16,400
I want a foreign mink coat,

604
00:26:16,640 --> 00:26:18,100
and I want silk stockings.

605
00:26:18,160 --> 00:26:20,220
You can tell at a glance she's no good.

606
00:26:22,160 --> 00:26:23,320
If it were you,

607
00:26:23,760 --> 00:26:25,040
would you be so willing

608
00:26:25,160 --> 00:26:26,620
to tell others about this?

609
00:26:30,560 --> 00:26:31,880
For Yunqi to do this,

610
00:26:32,640 --> 00:26:34,120
he must be facing some difficulties

611
00:26:34,120 --> 00:26:35,360
at the foreign firm.

612
00:26:35,920 --> 00:26:37,180
Yunqi is an honest man.

613
00:26:37,360 --> 00:26:38,280
As you just saw,

614
00:26:38,400 --> 00:26:39,680
he's just a bit henpecked.

615
00:26:39,680 --> 00:26:40,940
He's an honest person.

616
00:26:41,080 --> 00:26:42,080
Honest?

617
00:26:42,240 --> 00:26:43,520
Are you blind?

618
00:26:43,760 --> 00:26:45,040
Can't you see this couple

619
00:26:45,040 --> 00:26:46,640
is playing good cop, bad cop?

620
00:26:46,760 --> 00:26:48,080
They're putting on an act for you.

621
00:26:48,080 --> 00:26:49,400
They take you for a fool.

622
00:26:49,400 --> 00:26:50,860
Don't say that about them.

623
00:26:51,720 --> 00:26:53,320
Everything will be fine when the Elder Master returns.

624
00:26:53,320 --> 00:26:54,040
Madam,

625
00:26:54,160 --> 00:26:56,620
there's no need to wait for the Elder Master.

626
00:26:57,440 --> 00:26:58,300
Let me tell you.

627
00:27:01,720 --> 00:27:03,120
What is this dump?

628
00:27:09,640 --> 00:27:11,040
What are you laughing at?

629
00:27:11,200 --> 00:27:12,600
It's quite a coincidence

630
00:27:12,880 --> 00:27:14,340
that you bumped into them.

631
00:27:15,280 --> 00:27:16,960
No, I'm talking about serious business.

632
00:27:16,960 --> 00:27:17,840
Go ahead.

633
00:27:18,440 --> 00:27:19,920
We don't need to wait for Great-grandfather to come back.

634
00:27:19,920 --> 00:27:22,120
I know exactly how to deal with these people.

635
00:27:22,120 --> 00:27:24,720
Why don't you go down right now,

636
00:27:24,840 --> 00:27:25,760
keep a straight face,

637
00:27:25,760 --> 00:27:26,890
and tell that couple

638
00:27:26,960 --> 00:27:28,620
to kick that little vixen out.

639
00:27:28,720 --> 00:27:29,850
Tell her to get lost.

640
00:27:29,920 --> 00:27:31,440
If you're too embarrassed,

641
00:27:31,440 --> 00:27:33,080
then just pretend you didn't hear

642
00:27:33,080 --> 00:27:34,010
or see anything.

643
00:27:34,840 --> 00:27:36,040
I'll go straight down there,

644
00:27:36,040 --> 00:27:36,880
and give them a piece of my mind.

645
00:27:36,880 --> 00:27:37,480
In no time,

646
00:27:37,480 --> 00:27:39,080
I guarantee that little vixen won't be able to stay.

647
00:27:39,080 --> 00:27:40,040
She'll leave immediately.

648
00:27:40,040 --> 00:27:41,040
You can't do that.

649
00:27:41,680 --> 00:27:42,480
If you do that,

650
00:27:42,720 --> 00:27:44,600
where will Yunqi put his face?

651
00:27:45,120 --> 00:27:47,360
How can he show his face at the foreign firm?

652
00:27:47,360 --> 00:27:48,840
If he cared about his face,

653
00:27:49,280 --> 00:27:51,040
would he let you live here?

654
00:27:53,440 --> 00:27:54,720
He's not the same kind of person as you, the brigade commander,

655
00:27:54,720 --> 00:27:55,400
and Great-grandfather.

656
00:27:55,400 --> 00:27:56,680
Not at all.

657
00:27:57,240 --> 00:27:58,480
When we meet a gentleman,

658
00:27:58,480 --> 00:28:00,400
of course we treat him with respect.

659
00:28:00,400 --> 00:28:01,880
When we meet this kind of petty person,

660
00:28:01,880 --> 00:28:04,280
we have to use his own methods against him.

661
00:28:05,720 --> 00:28:06,920
Are you too embarrassed?

662
00:28:06,920 --> 00:28:07,920
Too proud to do it?

663
00:28:08,280 --> 00:28:10,280
Fine, I'll go right now.

664
00:28:10,960 --> 00:28:11,760
Wanfu.

665
00:28:13,800 --> 00:28:14,330
Don't go.

666
00:28:15,480 --> 00:28:16,280
Are you okay?

667
00:28:18,760 --> 00:28:20,720
Yunqi and Shuyuan

668
00:28:21,120 --> 00:28:22,840
are my family after all.

669
00:28:23,480 --> 00:28:24,340
We are a family.

670
00:28:24,440 --> 00:28:25,440
If you do this,

671
00:28:26,080 --> 00:28:28,160
where will Great-grandfather put his dignity?

672
00:28:28,160 --> 00:28:30,240
Who cares about dignity now?

673
00:28:30,480 --> 00:28:32,680
Look at these roof beams, do they treat you like family?

674
00:28:32,680 --> 00:28:33,560
If you don't think for yourself,

675
00:28:33,560 --> 00:28:35,220
you have to think for the baby.

676
00:28:35,560 --> 00:28:36,560
Don't worry about this.

677
00:28:36,560 --> 00:28:37,280
I'll go.

678
00:28:37,440 --> 00:28:38,720
I said don't go.

679
00:28:44,520 --> 00:28:46,920
Let's find Great-grandfather first.

680
00:28:50,120 --> 00:28:51,040
Fine.

681
00:28:52,080 --> 00:28:53,280
Why do I even care?

682
00:28:53,720 --> 00:28:55,580
I'll go find Great-grandfather.

683
00:29:47,840 --> 00:29:48,720
Baby,

684
00:29:48,720 --> 00:29:49,960
who is this?

685
00:29:51,080 --> 00:29:52,760
It's Daddy.

686
00:30:00,480 --> 00:30:03,520
After we find Daddy,

687
00:30:04,280 --> 00:30:06,560
and Grandpa comes back,

688
00:30:07,080 --> 00:30:08,640
we'll be reunited.

689
00:30:40,320 --> 00:30:44,720
The little baby's nose, eyes, and eyebrows,

690
00:30:45,280 --> 00:30:46,960
how good-looking they are.

691
00:30:48,240 --> 00:30:49,440
He completely inherited

692
00:30:49,440 --> 00:30:51,800
my older brother and sister-in-law's good traits.

693
00:30:51,800 --> 00:30:53,920
Just now, when I was holding the baby,

694
00:30:54,680 --> 00:30:57,040
I couldn't help but think,

695
00:31:01,400 --> 00:31:03,960
why is their life so good?

696
00:31:06,360 --> 00:31:08,800
It's too hard for us.

697
00:31:22,800 --> 00:31:24,480
The problem is with you.

698
00:31:25,600 --> 00:31:27,040
How is it my problem?

699
00:31:27,200 --> 00:31:28,360
It's clearly your problem.

700
00:31:28,360 --> 00:31:29,560
How is it my problem?

701
00:31:29,920 --> 00:31:31,600
I eat sea dragon, sea horse, and fur seal penis every day,

702
00:31:31,600 --> 00:31:31,960
so much of it,

703
00:31:31,960 --> 00:31:33,400
how could it be my problem?

704
00:31:33,400 --> 00:31:35,080
You eat sea dragon, sea horse, and fur seal penis every day,

705
00:31:35,080 --> 00:31:35,480
so much of it,

706
00:31:35,480 --> 00:31:36,440
and it still doesn't work,

707
00:31:36,440 --> 00:31:37,640
so it's your problem.

708
00:31:37,760 --> 00:31:38,800
I...

709
00:31:40,960 --> 00:31:42,620
I won't talk to you about this.

710
00:31:43,600 --> 00:31:44,680
But I still need to tell you something.

711
00:31:44,680 --> 00:31:45,940
I don't want to hear it.

712
00:31:46,040 --> 00:31:47,600
I'm not talking about the baby.

713
00:31:47,600 --> 00:31:48,680
The attic.

714
00:31:49,840 --> 00:31:50,720
Let me tell you,

715
00:31:50,960 --> 00:31:52,520
we still need to let my sister-in-law move downstairs.

716
00:31:52,520 --> 00:31:53,980
We'll move up to the attic.

717
00:31:54,800 --> 00:31:56,080
Are you crazy?

718
00:31:56,160 --> 00:31:58,040
You change your mind every second.

719
00:31:58,040 --> 00:31:59,880
When you helped her clean the attic just now,

720
00:31:59,880 --> 00:32:01,140
you were so energetic.

721
00:32:02,320 --> 00:32:04,320
What do you mean I change my mind every second?

722
00:32:04,320 --> 00:32:05,920
This house belongs to Uncle.

723
00:32:06,080 --> 00:32:08,280
It's only right for sister-in-law to live here.

724
00:32:08,280 --> 00:32:09,040
Don't forget,

725
00:32:09,040 --> 00:32:10,920
we're just looking after the house for them.

726
00:32:10,920 --> 00:32:12,360
Don't forget your place.

727
00:32:13,440 --> 00:32:16,200
And now you want me to move up to the attic?

728
00:32:16,240 --> 00:32:17,320
Don't forget

729
00:32:17,440 --> 00:32:19,570
how many people live in this big house,

730
00:32:19,720 --> 00:32:21,720
and I have to take care of everyone.

731
00:32:22,160 --> 00:32:23,720
I'm a tall person,

732
00:32:23,760 --> 00:32:25,220
crammed into the attic...

733
00:32:25,480 --> 00:32:26,120
To go to the bathroom,

734
00:32:26,120 --> 00:32:28,000
I'd have to go down ten thousand steps.

735
00:32:28,000 --> 00:32:29,860
You really know how to care for me.

736
00:32:30,120 --> 00:32:31,080
Go if you want,

737
00:32:31,280 --> 00:32:32,480
I'm not going anyway.

738
00:32:32,600 --> 00:32:34,260
You're just so unreasonable.

739
00:32:34,360 --> 00:32:35,640
Every time I try to reason with you,

740
00:32:35,640 --> 00:32:37,170
you never listen to reason.

741
00:32:38,000 --> 00:32:39,060
Sister-in-law...

742
00:32:39,480 --> 00:32:40,160
She is...

743
00:32:40,400 --> 00:32:41,760
my own sister-in-law.

744
00:32:42,560 --> 00:32:44,480
Of course she is.

745
00:32:44,720 --> 00:32:46,680
Look at the way you stare at her.

746
00:32:47,480 --> 00:32:49,640
If you want to fawn over her, go ahead.

747
00:32:49,880 --> 00:32:51,940
If you want to suck up to her, go ahead.

748
00:32:52,320 --> 00:32:53,450
What does this mean?

749
00:32:53,640 --> 00:32:54,560
Bringing three mouths,

750
00:32:54,560 --> 00:32:56,160
seeking refuge in our house.

751
00:32:56,480 --> 00:32:57,120
No,

752
00:32:57,280 --> 00:32:58,280
it should be four.

753
00:32:58,560 --> 00:32:59,960
There's also your Uncle.

754
00:33:00,360 --> 00:33:02,840
So I didn't get a single penny of rent,

755
00:33:02,840 --> 00:33:04,970
and I have to feed several more mouths.

756
00:33:05,080 --> 00:33:07,720
Li Shuyuan, you are so short-sighted.

757
00:33:08,440 --> 00:33:10,680
Our Zhang family has a lot of wealth, okay?

758
00:33:10,680 --> 00:33:11,960
When Uncle fled here,

759
00:33:12,080 --> 00:33:13,720
he must have brought plenty of gold and valuables.

760
00:33:13,720 --> 00:33:14,780
You won't lose out.

761
00:33:15,360 --> 00:33:17,820
Sister-in-law is a lady from a noble family.

762
00:33:18,320 --> 00:33:19,960
Well-educated and reasonable.

763
00:33:19,960 --> 00:33:21,400
She respects herself.

764
00:33:22,880 --> 00:33:24,400
That orderly beside her

765
00:33:24,880 --> 00:33:25,800
is very annoying.

766
00:33:25,800 --> 00:33:26,480
All day long,

767
00:33:26,480 --> 00:33:28,280
his big eyes are darting around.

768
00:33:28,360 --> 00:33:30,320
The first time I saw him, I wanted to kick him to death.

769
00:33:30,320 --> 00:33:32,720
I've been watching that shorty for a while.

770
00:33:32,760 --> 00:33:33,640
As soon as he came to our house,

771
00:33:33,640 --> 00:33:35,920
he was jumping up and down like a monkey,

772
00:33:36,320 --> 00:33:38,240
checking every room one by one.

773
00:33:38,360 --> 00:33:39,280
What's he trying to do?

774
00:33:39,280 --> 00:33:41,080
Is he scouting the terrain for a battle?

775
00:33:41,080 --> 00:33:42,340
Keep a close eye on him.

776
00:33:42,640 --> 00:33:44,440
He's harder to deal with than your sister-in-law.

777
00:33:44,440 --> 00:33:45,160
Got it.

778
00:33:46,080 --> 00:33:48,080
I heard your sister-in-law mention

779
00:33:48,440 --> 00:33:51,880
that Uncle has all the gold and jewelry.

780
00:33:52,280 --> 00:33:54,400
He must have the land deeds too.

781
00:33:58,760 --> 00:33:59,840
But the problem is,

782
00:34:00,480 --> 00:34:02,920
Uncle is wandering in the concessions,

783
00:34:03,160 --> 00:34:04,600
and it's chaos out there.

784
00:34:05,400 --> 00:34:06,840
What if...

785
00:34:08,000 --> 00:34:09,520
I'm just saying what if.

786
00:34:09,880 --> 00:34:11,540
What if something unexpected

787
00:34:11,639 --> 00:34:15,159
happens to Uncle?

788
00:34:28,440 --> 00:34:30,440
Li Shuyuan, you're out of your mind!

789
00:34:39,719 --> 00:34:40,840
Where are you going?

790
00:34:40,840 --> 00:34:41,840
To find Uncle.

791
00:34:42,159 --> 00:34:43,290
Where will you look?

792
00:34:43,679 --> 00:34:44,940
The refugee shelters.

793
00:34:45,320 --> 00:34:46,920
I know the concessions best.

794
00:34:46,920 --> 00:34:47,920
He's my own uncle.

795
00:34:48,000 --> 00:34:49,060
I'm his own nephew.

796
00:34:50,000 --> 00:34:51,000
If I don't go looking for him,

797
00:34:51,000 --> 00:34:52,120
am I even human?

798
00:34:52,520 --> 00:34:53,980
Now you're his own nephew.

799
00:34:54,480 --> 00:34:56,360
You're more filial than his own son.

800
00:34:56,360 --> 00:34:57,220
Let me tell you,

801
00:34:57,320 --> 00:34:58,560
you're not going anywhere today.

802
00:34:58,560 --> 00:35:00,360
I am going, and you can't stop me.

803
00:35:00,680 --> 00:35:01,880
What day is it today?

804
00:35:13,840 --> 00:35:16,000
Little... little guy.

805
00:35:19,040 --> 00:35:20,320
Go wash your feet.

806
00:35:31,120 --> 00:35:31,960
Here,

807
00:35:32,320 --> 00:35:33,640
take it easy.

808
00:35:34,800 --> 00:35:36,680
Brother, I have a child with me,

809
00:35:36,680 --> 00:35:37,800
could I have another portion?

810
00:35:37,800 --> 00:35:38,400
You can't take two portions

811
00:35:38,400 --> 00:35:39,640
just for yourself.

812
00:35:40,440 --> 00:35:42,240
How about this: you eat first,

813
00:35:42,240 --> 00:35:44,040
then come back for more when you're done, okay?

814
00:35:44,040 --> 00:35:44,800
Okay.

815
00:35:45,320 --> 00:35:45,960
Thank you.

816
00:35:46,080 --> 00:35:46,560
No problem.

817
00:35:46,560 --> 00:35:48,820
Slow down, careful not to burn the child.

818
00:35:49,120 --> 00:35:50,720
Hey, what are you doing?

819
00:35:51,200 --> 00:35:52,460
Everyone is lining up.

820
00:35:53,240 --> 00:35:54,040
Go line up at the back.

821
00:35:54,040 --> 00:35:54,770
Okay, going.

822
00:35:54,800 --> 00:35:55,480
Hurry up.

823
00:35:56,800 --> 00:35:57,800
Don't rush.

824
00:35:57,800 --> 00:35:58,360
Here.

825
00:36:00,120 --> 00:36:01,650
Careful, don't get burned.

826
00:36:01,720 --> 00:36:02,800
Next, next.

827
00:36:04,480 --> 00:36:05,610
Here, this is yours.

828
00:36:06,800 --> 00:36:07,680
Slow down.

829
00:36:15,000 --> 00:36:16,200
Want some wontons?

830
00:36:16,480 --> 00:36:18,360
Large or small?

831
00:36:20,960 --> 00:36:22,720
Cigarettes, selling cigarettes!

832
00:36:22,720 --> 00:36:24,160
Excuse me, coming through!

833
00:36:24,160 --> 00:36:25,160
Selling flatbread!

834
00:36:25,160 --> 00:36:27,960
Cigarettes, selling cigarettes!

835
00:36:42,360 --> 00:36:43,080
Excuse me.

836
00:36:43,760 --> 00:36:44,440
Could I ask,

837
00:36:44,720 --> 00:36:46,720
why is the newspaper office closed?

838
00:36:47,920 --> 00:36:50,120
It's all because of their pro-resistance articles.

839
00:36:50,120 --> 00:36:50,960
The Japanese

840
00:36:51,520 --> 00:36:53,320
protest to the concession authorities every day.

841
00:36:53,320 --> 00:36:55,000
The French Municipal Council and the Municipal Council

842
00:36:55,000 --> 00:36:56,800
reached an agreement with them.

843
00:36:57,000 --> 00:36:58,520
All anti-Japanese newspapers

844
00:36:58,520 --> 00:36:59,760
have suspended publication.

845
00:36:59,760 --> 00:37:00,920
A janitor like me

846
00:37:01,320 --> 00:37:03,320
can only sell potstickers here now.

847
00:37:03,960 --> 00:37:06,560
Our president was targeted by Japanese agents

848
00:37:06,720 --> 00:37:08,520
just because he published the words,

849
00:37:08,520 --> 00:37:11,240
'Chinese people, Chinese newspaper, no surrender, no humiliation.'

850
00:37:11,240 --> 00:37:13,170
He was targeted by Japanese agents

851
00:37:13,720 --> 00:37:14,600
and shot dead

852
00:37:15,080 --> 00:37:17,280
on his way home from work.

853
00:37:17,960 --> 00:37:18,560
Stop!

854
00:37:19,360 --> 00:37:19,960
Don't run!

855
00:37:20,480 --> 00:37:20,880
Stop!

856
00:37:21,920 --> 00:37:23,000
Stop!

857
00:37:24,920 --> 00:37:26,380
National Salvation Times

858
00:37:26,400 --> 00:37:27,860
is completely disbanded.

859
00:37:29,000 --> 00:37:31,600
The editors are all finding their own ways out.

860
00:37:31,960 --> 00:37:33,160
It will be hard for you

861
00:37:33,800 --> 00:37:35,080
to find them again.

862
00:37:37,880 --> 00:37:39,120
Rich or poor,

863
00:37:39,760 --> 00:37:41,290
don't let the child suffer.

864
00:37:41,520 --> 00:37:43,360
Come on, take it.

865
00:37:45,640 --> 00:37:47,000
Take it.

866
00:37:50,480 --> 00:37:51,720
Thank you.

867
00:39:02,120 --> 00:39:03,080
Stop!

868
00:39:12,640 --> 00:39:14,240
There's one in uniform over there.

869
00:39:14,240 --> 00:39:15,240
Bring him here.

870
00:39:16,560 --> 00:39:17,620
Are you a deserter?

871
00:39:17,640 --> 00:39:18,900
No, I'm not a deserter.

872
00:39:19,040 --> 00:39:20,040
Which unit are you from?

873
00:39:20,040 --> 00:39:22,120
The 211st Regiment, 106th Brigade.

874
00:39:22,440 --> 00:39:23,480
By order of the commander-in-chief,

875
00:39:23,480 --> 00:39:25,320
all stragglers will be incorporated by our unit.

876
00:39:25,320 --> 00:39:26,320
Let's go. Keep up.

877
00:39:26,840 --> 00:39:27,370
Let's go.

878
00:39:33,040 --> 00:39:33,880
Let's go.

879
00:39:41,440 --> 00:39:42,360
Which unit?

880
00:39:42,440 --> 00:39:43,600
What's your name?

881
00:39:45,400 --> 00:39:47,200
Speak! Are you out of your mind?

882
00:39:47,320 --> 00:39:50,250
If you don't speak, you will be treated as a deserter.

883
00:39:50,600 --> 00:39:51,640
Sir,

884
00:39:51,720 --> 00:39:54,200
I am a cook from the directly subordinate team of the 87th Brigade.

885
00:39:54,200 --> 00:39:55,280
Kong Erbao.

886
00:39:57,120 --> 00:39:58,200
The 87th Brigade.

887
00:39:58,680 --> 00:40:00,560
I've collected so many stragglers.

888
00:40:00,560 --> 00:40:02,960
You are the first one from the 87th Brigade.

889
00:40:03,200 --> 00:40:04,480
You are very lucky.

890
00:40:04,760 --> 00:40:05,880
I heard that your brigade

891
00:40:05,880 --> 00:40:08,120
was wiped out during the Battle of Shanghai.

892
00:40:08,120 --> 00:40:08,960
Yes.

893
00:40:09,760 --> 00:40:11,090
They all died in battle.

894
00:40:14,760 --> 00:40:16,600
By order of the commander-in-chief of the war zone,

895
00:40:16,600 --> 00:40:19,360
our unit is responsible for incorporating all stragglers.

896
00:40:19,360 --> 00:40:20,280
You should come with us.

897
00:40:20,280 --> 00:40:21,160
Yes, sir.

898
00:40:21,400 --> 00:40:22,480
Fall in.

899
00:40:30,040 --> 00:40:30,800
Sir.

900
00:40:30,880 --> 00:40:32,210
Which unit are you from?

901
00:40:32,440 --> 00:40:34,120
We are the 41st Army,

902
00:40:34,560 --> 00:40:36,080
transferred from Sichuan.

903
00:40:36,080 --> 00:40:37,880
We walked over a thousand miles.

904
00:40:37,920 --> 00:40:38,960
Before we could even sit down,

905
00:40:38,960 --> 00:40:40,560
we were sent out to pick up people.

906
00:40:40,560 --> 00:40:41,320
Yes, yes.

907
00:40:41,520 --> 00:40:42,920
You've worked hard, sir.

908
00:40:43,040 --> 00:40:43,800
Sir.

909
00:40:44,120 --> 00:40:45,800
Where are we going next?

910
00:40:46,120 --> 00:40:47,120
All the way north.

911
00:40:47,360 --> 00:40:48,440
To the Fifth War Zone.

912
00:40:48,440 --> 00:40:49,560
The Fifth War Zone.

913
00:40:50,280 --> 00:40:51,120
Where exactly?

914
00:40:51,120 --> 00:40:53,080
Bengbu or Xuzhou?

915
00:40:53,520 --> 00:40:54,580
You're just a cook,

916
00:40:54,720 --> 00:40:56,580
but you guess pretty accurately.

917
00:40:56,840 --> 00:40:58,920
It's Northern Jiangsu, the Xuzhou War Zone.

918
00:40:58,920 --> 00:41:01,320
To join up with Commander Sun's 141st Army.

919
00:41:02,120 --> 00:41:03,080
The 141st Army.

920
00:41:03,480 --> 00:41:04,360
Commander Sun.

921
00:41:05,040 --> 00:41:07,600
I think his name is Sun something-yi.

922
00:41:08,960 --> 00:41:09,680
Sun Huaiyi.

923
00:41:09,760 --> 00:41:10,360
Yes.

924
00:41:10,800 --> 00:41:12,730
I think he is your former superior.

925
00:41:13,200 --> 00:41:14,730
He is now a corps commander.

926
00:41:14,880 --> 00:41:16,210
The Battle of Shanghai.

927
00:41:16,280 --> 00:41:19,320
Division Commander Sun planned properly and commanded well.

928
00:41:19,320 --> 00:41:21,960
He is now transferred to the Fifth War Zone as the Army Commander.

929
00:41:21,960 --> 00:41:23,690
Hey, you in front, walk faster!

930
00:41:33,840 --> 00:41:35,970
You shouldn't have come out to do this.

931
00:41:36,360 --> 00:41:38,020
You should be resting at home.

932
00:41:38,560 --> 00:41:40,090
I can't stay at home anyway.

933
00:41:41,640 --> 00:41:42,840
Pardon me for asking.

934
00:41:46,400 --> 00:41:47,730
Where is your bracelet?

935
00:41:52,600 --> 00:41:56,000
Shuyuan has been managing the whole family.

936
00:41:56,360 --> 00:41:58,160
She paid for all the expenses.

937
00:41:58,520 --> 00:41:59,840
With a few more mouths to feed,

938
00:41:59,840 --> 00:42:01,040
we can't let her suffer a loss.

939
00:42:01,040 --> 00:42:01,880
Bah!

940
00:42:02,000 --> 00:42:03,240
What loss is she suffering?

941
00:42:03,240 --> 00:42:03,920
This gossipy woman

942
00:42:03,920 --> 00:42:05,520
is just thinking about the master's money

943
00:42:05,520 --> 00:42:06,450
and title deeds.

944
00:42:06,640 --> 00:42:09,300
You shouldn't have told her the truth back then.

945
00:42:09,320 --> 00:42:10,720
This house is yours anyway.

946
00:42:10,720 --> 00:42:12,050
If you collect the rent,

947
00:42:12,200 --> 00:42:13,400
not to mention you and the kids,

948
00:42:13,400 --> 00:42:15,120
the master, me, Aunt Liu,

949
00:42:15,360 --> 00:42:16,820
it's enough for five of us.

950
00:42:19,640 --> 00:42:20,240
Okay.

951
00:42:20,520 --> 00:42:21,650
I won't say anymore.

952
00:42:21,760 --> 00:42:23,890
If I say too much, I'm just an outsider.

953
00:42:29,320 --> 00:42:30,840
We've put it in the newspaper

954
00:42:30,840 --> 00:42:32,800
and posted missing person notices.

955
00:42:32,800 --> 00:42:35,320
I've been to the police station and the refugee camp.

956
00:42:35,320 --> 00:42:36,440
In this tiny concession,

957
00:42:36,440 --> 00:42:38,120
where could the master go?

958
00:42:44,600 --> 00:42:45,640
I heard that

959
00:42:46,280 --> 00:42:47,160
recently in the concession,

960
00:42:47,160 --> 00:42:49,560
the streets are full of homeless refugees.

961
00:42:49,680 --> 00:42:52,360
Every night, people freeze or starve to death.

962
00:42:52,600 --> 00:42:54,480
Shoushantang even has a special corpse transport team.

963
00:42:54,480 --> 00:42:56,720
Every morning, they take the corpses on the road

964
00:42:56,720 --> 00:42:59,920
and bury them in the wilderness.

965
00:43:00,320 --> 00:43:00,800
No, no.

966
00:43:01,400 --> 00:43:02,120
Madam, no.

967
00:43:02,560 --> 00:43:03,960
I didn't mean that.
